|0||2||0||16||6\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Everton F.C. season|2010\u201311]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|29||3||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||33||3\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Everton F.C. season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|2||1||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!174!!28!!21!!3!!14!!4!!209!!35\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Arsenal F.C. season|2011\u201312]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|rowspan=\"5\"|Premier League\n|29||6||3||0||6||0||38||6\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Arsenal F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|34||6||2||0||7||0||43||6\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Arsenal F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|31||2||6||1||6||0||43||3\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Arsenal F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|7||0||1||0||4||1||12||1\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Arsenal F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=PremProfile/>\n|9||0||4||0||1||0||14||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!110!!14!!16!!1!!24!!1!!150!!16\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!422!!60!!58!!7!!59!!7!!539!!74\n|}\n\n:<div id=\"1\"><sup>1</sup> <small> Includes [[Coupe de France]], [[Coupe de la Ligue]], [[Scottish Cup]], [[Scottish League Cup]], [[FA Cup]] and [[EFL Cup|Football League Cup]]</small> </div>\n\n===Managerial record===\n{{updated|match played 7th March 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Managerial record by team and tenure\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Team\n!rowspan=2|From\n!rowspan=2|To\n!colspan=5|Record\n!rowspan=2|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!{{abbr|P|Matches played}}!!{{abbr|W|Matches won}}!!{{abbr|D|Matches drawn}}!!{{abbr|L|Matches lost}}!!{{abbr|Win %|Win percentage}}\n|-\n|align=left|[[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]\n|align=left|20 December 2019\n|align=left|''Present''\n{{WDL|16|8|6|2}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sofascore.com/manager/mikel-arteta/794075 |title=Mikel Arteta managerial statistics |website=SofaScore |accessdate=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n{{WDLtot|16|8|6|2}}\n!\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Paris Saint-Germain'''\n*[[UEFA Intertoto Cup]]: [[2001 UEFA Intertoto Cup|2001]]<ref>{{cite news \n|url=https://www.repubblica.it/online/sport/intertoto/uefa/uefa.html\n|title= Brescia, sogno finito il Psg va in Uefa\n|publisher=Repubblica.it\n|accessdate=2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Rangers'''\n*[[Scottish Premier League]]: [[2002\u201303 Scottish Premier League|2002\u201303]]<ref>{{cite book |editor1-first=Glenda |editor1-last=Rollin |editor2-first=Jack |editor2-last=Rollin |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2003\u20132004 |year=2003 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-0-7553-1228-3 |pages=698\u2013699, 712}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish League Cup]]: [[2002\u201303 Scottish League Cup|2002\u201303]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_div_1/2853133.stm |title=Rangers retain CIS Cup |website=BBC Sport |date=16 March 2003 |accessdate=3 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Arsenal'''\n*[[FA Cup]]: [[2013\u201314 FA Cup|2013\u201314]],<ref name=2014FACupFinal/> [[2014\u201315 FA Cup|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32856754 |title=Arsenal 4\u20130 Aston Villa |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2015 |accessdate=3 December 2019}}<br />{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/fa-cup-final-arsenal-thrash-villa-828gx85h3v3 |title=FA Cup final: Arsenal thrash Villa |first=Howard |last=Swains |newspaper=The Times |location=London |date=30 May 2015 |accessdate=3 December 2019 |url-access=registration |quote=Mikel Arteta, the Arsenal club captain, leads the team up the famous stairs and is first to collect his winner's medal from Prince William.}}</ref>\n*[[FA Community Shield]]: [[2014 FA Community Shield|2014]],<ref name=2014CommunityShield/> [[2015 FA Community Shield|2015]]<ref name=2015CommunityShield/>\n\n'''Spain U16'''\n*[[UEFA European Under-16 Championship]]: [[1999 UEFA European Under-16 Championship|1999]]<ref name=RSSSF>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/ec-u16-99.html |title=European U16 Football Championship 1999 |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation}}</ref>\n\n'''Spain U18'''\n*[[UEFA\u2013CAF Meridian Cup]]: [[1999 UEFA\u2013CAF Meridian Cup|1999]]{{citation needed|date=December 2019}}\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[List of Scottish Premier League monthly award winners|Scottish Premier League Young Player of the Month]]: September 2002, August 2003<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.myfootballfacts.com/world-football/scottish-football/spl_manager_and_player_of_the_month_awards/|title=Scottish Premier League / Scottish Professional Football League Manager and Player of the Month Award 2000\u201301 to 2018\u201319\n|website=My Football Facts|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n*[[List of Everton F.C. records and statistics#Evertonfc.com player awards|Everton Player of the Season]]: [[2005\u201306 Everton F.C. season|2005\u201306]], [[2006\u201307 Everton F.C. season|2006\u201307]]<ref name=EFC />\n*[[List of Everton F.C. records and statistics#Evertonfc.com player awards|Everton Players' Player of the Season]]: 2005\u201306<ref name=EFC />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20111129122147/http://www.arsenal.com/first-team/players/mikel-arteta Arsenal F.C. Profile]\n*{{BDFutbol}}\n*[http://www.fitbastats.com/rangers/player.php?playerid=1219 Rangers profile at ''fitbastats.com'']\n*{{Soccerway}}\n*{{LFP}}\n\n{{Arsenal F.C. squad}}\n{{Premier League managers}}\n{{Everton F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{Arsenal F.C. managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Arteta, Mikel}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from San Sebasti\u00e1n]]\n[[Category:Basque footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Antiguoko players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona C players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona B players]]\n[[Category:Paris Saint-Germain F.C. players]]\n[[