|align=center|0\u20131\n|align=center|8\u20132\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol keep vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|3QR\n|{{flagicon|ROM}} [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]]\n|align=center|1\u20133\n|align=center|0\u20133\n|align=center|1\u20136\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[2010\u201311 Motherwell F.C. season|2010\u201311]]\n|rowspan=3|[[2010\u201311 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n|2QR\n|{{flagicon|ISL}} [[Brei\u00f0ablik UBK|Brei\u00f0ablik]]\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|align=center|1\u20130\n|align=center|2\u20130\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol keep vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|3QR\n|{{flagicon|NOR}} [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]]\n|align=center|3\u20130\n|align=center|1\u20131\n|align=center|4\u20131\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol keep vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|PO\n|{{flagicon|DEN}} [[Odense Boldklub|Odense]]\n|align=center|0\u20131\n|align=center|1\u20132\n|align=center|1\u20133\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[2012\u201313 Motherwell F.C. season|2012\u201313]]\n\n|[[2012\u201313 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]]\n|3QR\n|{{flagicon|GRE}} [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|align=center|0\u20132\n|align=center|0\u20133\n|align=center|0\u20135\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n|PO\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Levante UD|Levante]]\n|align=center|0\u20132\n|align=center|0\u20131\n|align=center|0\u20133\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Motherwell F.C. season|2013\u201314]]\n|[[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n|3QR\n|{{flagicon|RUS}} [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|Kuban Krasnodar]]\n|align=center|0\u20132\n|align=center|0\u20131\n|align=center|0\u20133\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Motherwell F.C. season|2014\u201315]]\n|[[2014\u201315 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]\n|2QR\n|{{flagicon|ISL}} [[Stjarnan]]\n|align=center|2\u20132\n|align=center|2\u20133\n|align=center|4\u20135\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n|align=center|[[After extra time|Extra time]]\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n===By competition===\n{| class=\"wikitable unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center\" width=\"50%\"\n|-\n! Competition !! {{Tooltip|P|Played}} !! {{Tooltip|W|Wins}} !! {{Tooltip|D|Draws}} !! {{Tooltip|L|Losses}} !! {{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}} !! {{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}} !! {{Tooltip|GD|Goal difference}}\n|-\n| [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]] ||width=\"7%\"| 2 ||width=\"7%\"| 1 ||width=\"7%\"| 0 ||width=\"7%\"| 1 ||width=\"7%\"| 3 ||width=\"7%\"| 3 ||width=\"7%\"| 0\n|-\n| [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] / [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] || 26 || 8 || 2 || 16 || 33 || 34 || 0\n|-\n| [[European Cup]] / [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] || 2 || 0 || 0 || 2 || 0 || 5 || \u22125\n|-\n! Total || 30 || 9 || 2 || 19 || 36 || 42 || -6\n|}\n\n===By country===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Country\n!scope=\"col\"|Pld\n!scope=\"col\"|W\n!scope=\"col\"|D\n!scope=\"col\"|L\n!scope=\"col\"|GF\n!scope=\"col\"|GA\n!scope=\"col\"|GD\n!scope=\"col\"|Win%\n!scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Ref\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Albania}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=8|against=2|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Denmark}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=1|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Faroe Islands}}\n{{WDL|2|2|0|0|for=7|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Finland}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=3|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|France}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=0|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Germany}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=0|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Greece}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=0|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Iceland}}\n{{WDL|4|2|1|1|for=6|against=5|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Norway}}\n{{WDL|2|1|1|0|for=4|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Poland}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=3|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Romania}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=1|against=6|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Russia}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=0|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Spain}}\n{{WDL|2|0|0|2|for=0|against=3|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" align=left|{{flag|Wales}}\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|for=3|against=1|diff=yes}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.motherwell-mad.co.uk/feat/edz9/well_in_europe_section/index.shtml Motherwell European Record] at Fir Park Corner\n\n{{Motherwell F.C.}}\n{{Scottish football clubs in Europe}}\n\n[[Category:Motherwell F.C.]]\n[[Category:Scottish football clubs in European football|Motherwell]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2017}}\n{{infobox continental football\n| continent        = Europe\n| title            = Motherwell in European football\n| image            = \n| club             = [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]\n| caption          = \n| first entry      = [[1991\u201392 European Cup Winners' Cup]]<ref name=\"RSSSF_Fairs_Cup\"/>\n| last entry       = [[2014\u201315 UEFA Europa League]]<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2014/clubs/club=53035/profile/index.html Motherwell FC], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. Retrieved 8 August 2013.</ref>\n| european cup     = 0 (Best: Third Qualifying round)\n| uefa cup         = 0 (Best: Play-off round)\n| cup winners' cup = 0 (Best: First round)\n| intertoto cup    = \n| uefa super cup   = \n}}\n[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell Football Club]] is a [[football in Scotland|Scottish football]] club based in the town of [[Motherwell]], [[North Lanarkshire]]. The club first competed in a European competition in [[1991\u201392 European Cup Winners' Cup|1991\u201392]], qualifying for the [[European Cup Winners' Cup]] as winners of the [[1991 Scottish Cup Final|1991 Scottish Cup]].<ref name=\"RSSSF_Fairs_Cup\">[http://www.rsssf.com/ec/ec199192.html#cwc 1991-92], ''[[RSSSF|rsssf.com]]''. 17 January 2008. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> The club have reached the play-off round of the [[Europa League]] twice (2010<ref name=\"10-11\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2011/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2010/11 Europa League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 13 August 2011. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> and 2012<ref name=\"12-13\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2013/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2012/13 Europa League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 31 August 2012. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref>), which remains the club's joint best run in a European competition.\n\n==History==\n===1990s===\nMotherwell qualified for a UEFA competition for the first time in 1991\u201392 after winning the [[Scottish Cup]] the previous season. Their opponents were [[GKS Katowice]] from [[Poland]]. They won the home leg 3-1, but lost the away tie 2-0, resulting in elimination on away goals.<ref name=\"RSSSF_Fairs_Cup\"/>\n\nMotherwell qualified for the UEFA Cup for the first time in 1994\u201395 having finished third in the [[1993\u201394 Scottish Premier Division]] the previous season. They faced [[HB Torshavn]] of the [[Faroe Islands]] in the preliminary round, and advanced to the next round winning by an aggregate score of 7-1 after a 3-0 home leg win.<ref name=\"94-95\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=1994/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 1994/95 UEFA Cup], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 12 August 2011. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> In the first round proper, they faced [[Germany|German]] giants [[Borussia Dortmund]]. They lost the first leg away 1-0 and lost the home second leg 2-0, losing 3-0 on aggregate.<ref name=\"94-95\"/> Motherwell finished second behind [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] in the [[1994\u201395 Scottish Premier Division]], leading to qualification for the preliminary round of the [[UEFA Cup]]. They faced [[MYPA]] of [[Finland]], but lost the first leg 3-1 at home. A 2-0 away win was not enough for Motherwell to advance and they were eliminated on the [[away goals rule]].<ref name=\"95-96\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=1995/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 1995/96 UEFA Cup], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 12 August 2011. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref>\n\n===2008&ndash;15===\nAfter a 13-year absence, Motherwell returned to European football by finishing third in the [[2007-08 Scottish Premier League]]. They were drawn to face [[AS Nancy|Nancy]] of [[France]] in the first round proper. After losing the first leg 1-0 at the [[Stade Marcel Picot]], they then lost the second leg 2-0 at home, losing 3-0 on aggregate.<ref name=\"08-09\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2009/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2008/09 UEFA Cup], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 13 August 2011. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> Motherwell qualified for Europe for a second straight season after winning a place through the [[UEFA Respect Fair Play ranking|Fair Play League]], despite finishing 7th the previous season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8039270.stm|title=Scots win Fair Play European spot|work=BBC Sport|publisher=[[British Broadcasting Corporation|BBC]]|date=8 May 2009|accessdate=September 2012}}</ref> They were the first ever Scottish entrant to the newly formed Europa League. Also, due to extensive remedial work on their [[Fir Park]] surface, Motherwell played all of their home European matches at [[Excelsior Stadium]] in [[Airdrie, North Lanarkshire|Airdrie]]. They were drawn to face [[Welsh Premier League]] side [[Llanelli A.F.C.|Llanelli]] in the first qualifying round. They suffered a shock 1-0 home first leg defeat, but recovered to win the away leg 3-0 at the [[Parc y Scarlets]].<ref name=\"09-10\">[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2010/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2009/10 Europa League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 13 August 2011. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> In the next round they met [[KS Flamurtari Vlor\u00eb|Flamurtari]] of [[Albania]], but lost the first leg 1-0 away. Just like in the previous round, they recovered by hammering the Albanians 8-1 at home in the second, a score that stands as a record club European victory to this day.<ref name=\"09-10\"/> They advanced to the third qualifying round for a meeting with [[Romania]]n heavyweights [[FC Steaua Bucure\u0219ti|Steaua Bucure\u0219ti]]. They lost the first leg 3-0 away at the [[Stadionul Steaua (1974)|Stadionul Steaua]], and the second leg 3-1 at home. and were eliminated 6-1 on aggregate.<ref name=\"09-10\"/> \n\nA fifth-place finish in the [[2010-11 Scottish Premier League]] saw Motherwell qualify for Europe for a third straight season. They were to play only [[Scandinavia]]n opponents during that season's run. They first played [[Iceland]]ic club [[Brei\u00f0ablik UBK|Brei\u00f0ablik]] in the second qualifying round, winning both legs 1-0 to advance to the third qualifying round.<ref name=\"10-11\"/> They would then be paired with [[Aalesunds FK|Aalesunds]] of [[Norway]], and drew the first leg away 1-1, their only draw in European football, before winning the second leg 3-0 at [[Fir Park]].<ref name=\"10-11\"/> They were in the Europa League play-offs, the furthest they have gone in European competition, and would play [[Denmark|Danish]] outfit [[Odense Boldklub|Odense]]. They lost the first leg away 2-1, and lost the home second leg 1-0 to  bow out of Europe for another season.<ref name=\"10-11\"/>\n\nMotherwell qualified for the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] for the first time in 2012, being placed in the third qualifying round. They took the place of [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] who were in [[Administration (British football)|administration]] and were not allowed to participate. Motherwell were in the non-champions section of the draw, and were paired with [[Greece|Greek]] giants [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]. They lost the first leg 2-0 at Fir Park, and went on to lose the second leg 3-0 at the [[Olympic Stadium (Athens)|Olympic Stadium]] in [[Athens]].<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2013/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2012/13 UEFA Champions League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 31 August 2012. Retrieved 5 September 2012.</ref> Motherwell's elimination from the Champions League saw them parachuted into the Europa League play-off round, where they would face [[Levante UD|Levante]] of [[Spain]]. After losing the home leg 2-0, they then lost the second leg 1-0 away in [[Valencia]] to bow out of Europe 3-0 on aggregate and without scoring a single goal overall.<ref name=\"12-13\"/> They did, however, equal their longest participation in European competition.\n\nMotherwell finished the [[2012-13 Scottish Premier League]] in second place, and with champions [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] winning the [[2012-13 Scottish Cup]], Motherwell moved into the third qualifying round of the Europa League. They were un-seeded in that draw and were paired with [[FC Kuban Krasnodar|Kuban Krasnodar]] of [[Russia]]. They lost the first-leg 2-0 at Fir Park, suffering a 1-0 defeat in the return leg to exit European competition.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2014/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2013/14 UEFA Europa League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 8 August 2013. Retrieved 8 August 2013.</ref> Motherwell finished the [[2013-14 Scottish Premiership]] in second place, meaning Motherwell began in the second qualifying round of the Europa League. They were seeded in that draw and were paired with [[Stjarnan]] of [[Iceland]]. They drew the first-leg 2-2 at Fir Park, suffering a 3-2 extra-time defeat in the return leg to suffer elimination from that season's competition.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2015/clubs/club=53035/matches/index.html 2014/15 UEFA Europa League], ''[[UEFA|uefa.com]]''. 22 September 2014. Retrieved 22 September 2014.</ref>\n\n==Overall record==\n===Matches===\n{|class=\"sortable plainrowheaders wikitable\" width=\"65%\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#EFEFEF;\" colspan=17 | List of Motherwell games in European competitions\n|-\n! Season\n! Competition\n! Round\n! Opponent\n! Home\n! Away\n! Other\n! [[Two-legged tie|Agg.]]\n! scope=\"col\" width=15|{{efn|Round or group progressed ([[File:Symbol keep vote.svg|17px]]) or eliminated ([[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]])}}\n!class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n!class=\"unsortable\"| Ref\n|-\n|[[1991\u201392 Motherwell F.C. season|1991\u201392]]\n|[[1991\u201392 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n|1R\n|{{flagicon|POL}} [[GKS Katowice]]\n|align=center|3\u20131\n|align=center|0\u20132\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"20\" {{n/a}}\n|align=center|3\u20133\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n|align=center|[[Away goals rule|Away goals]]\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[1994\u201395 Motherwell F.C. season|1994\u201395]]\n|rowspan=2|[[1994\u201395 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n|PR\n|{{flagicon|Faroe Islands}} [[HB Torshavn]]\n|align=center|3\u20130\n|align=center|4\u20131\n|align=center|7\u20131\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol keep vote.svg|17px]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a}}\n| \n|-\n|1R\n|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n|align=center|0\u20132\n|align=center|0\u20131\n|align=center|0\u20133\n| style=\"text-align:center;| [[File:Symbol delete vote.svg|17px]]\n| \n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Motherwell F.C. season|1995\u201396]]\n|[[1995\u201396 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]\n|PR\n|{{flagicon|FIN}} [[MYPA|MyPA-47]]\n|align=center|1\u20133\n|align=center|2\u20130\n|align=center|3\u20